This paper discusses the anonymity network I2P and its resistance to censorship, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The study also involves measuring network properties and analyzing network structure, which could fall under the categories of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The discussion of potential approaches to make I2P more resistant to blocking could also fall under the categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and performance (cs.PF).
